    skos:definition "Specific legal provision granting the Court of Justice unlimited jurisdiction with regard to penalties"@en .

euai:ARTICLE_26_8_ a owl:NamedIndividual,
        euai:Article ;
    rdfs:label "ARTICLE 26(8)"@en ;
    skos:definition "Provision requiring data protection impact assessments to be summarized during registration"@en .

euai:ARTICLE_27 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        euai:Article ;
    rdfs:label "ARTICLE 27"@en ;
    skos:definition "**ARTICLE 27** is a regulatory provision that mandates the completion of a fundamental rights impact assessment. This requirement specifically applies to the deployers of certain high-risk AI systems. As a key component of the regulatory framework, Article 27 functions to ensure that organizations or entities utilizing these high-risk technologies rigorously evaluate and address the potential implications their systems may have on fundamental rights. By requiring this assessment, the article est"@en .

euai:ARTICLE_27_OF_DIRECTIVE__EU__2016_680 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        euai:Article ;
    rdfs:label "ARTICLE 27 OF DIRECTIVE (EU) 2016/680"@en ;
    skos:definition "Article governing data protection impact assessments under the Law Enforcement Directive"@en .

euai:ARTICLE_28 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        euai:Article ;
    rdfs:label "ARTICLE 28"@en ;
    skos:definition "**ARTICLE 28** serves as the regulatory framework establishing the duties, operational requirements, and specific roles of Notifying Authorities. This article defines the fundamental responsibilities that these authorities must uphold to ensure compliance and proper functioning within their designated regulatory scope. It outlines not only the obligations required of these entities but also sets the operational standards they must meet to effectively fulfill their oversight and notification mand"@en .

euai:ARTICLE_2_TEU a owl:NamedIndividual,
        euai:Article ;
    rdfs:label "ARTICLE 2 TEU"@en ;
    skos:definition "Reference to Union values upon which AI and its regulatory framework must be developed"@en .

euai:ARTICLE_30_OF_REGULATION__EU__2019_1020 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        euai:Article ;
    rdfs:label "ARTICLE 30 OF REGULATION (EU) 2019/1020"@en ;
    skos:definition "Legal basis defining the administrative cooperation group (ADCO) which the standing sub-group for market surveillance acts as."@en .

euai:ARTICLE_34 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        euai:Article ;
    rdfs:label "ARTICLE 34"@en ;
    skos:definition "Article 34 serves as a regulatory provision that explicitly defines the obligations of notified bodies. This article specifically outlines the operational responsibilities that these entities must adhere to in the execution of their duties."@en ;
    euai:definedInArticle euai:PENALTIES_FOR_GENERAL_NON_COMPLIANCE .

euai:ARTICLE_36 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        euai:Article ;
    rdfs:label "ARTICLE 36"@en ;
    skos:definition "Article concerning changes to notifications, including cessation of activities, suspension, and withdrawal of designation"@en ;
    euai:definedInArticle euai:ARTICLE_29,
