    rdfs:label "COMMISSION"@en ;
    skos:definition "The European Commission serves as the central regulatory and executive authority under the EU AI Act, wielding extensive powers to oversee, enforce, and adapt the Regulation to evolving technological landscapes. As the EU executive body, the European Commission is responsible for the overall implementation of the Regulation, which includes establishing the AI Office, appointing the AI High-Level Expert Group (HLEG), and maintaining the European Artificial Intelligence Board. It acts as the contr"@en ;
