    rdfs:label "EUROPEAN COMMISSION"@en ;
    skos:definition """The European Commission functions as the central executive institution of the European Union, playing a comprehensive and multifaceted role in the implementation, oversight, and enforcement of the AI Act. As the body responsible for proposing the legislation, the European Commission is tasked with the ongoing evaluation and review of the Regulation, including a formal assessment of its enforcement by August 2031, which it reports to the European Parliament and the Council.

A primary responsibil"""@en ;
