euai:ARTICLE_5 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        euai:Article ;
    rdfs:label "ARTICLE 5"@en ;
    skos:definition """**Article 5** of the AI Act serves as a foundational provision governing prohibited AI practices. It establishes a definitive list of AI systems and practices that are banned within the European Union, primarily due to their unacceptable risk to fundamental rights and societal values.

Central to the scope of Article 5 are specific prohibitions regarding biometric identification and categorization. These include restrictions on predictive policing, untargeted scraping of facial images from the i"""@en ;
    euai:definedInArticle euai:PENALTIES_FOR_PROHIBITED_PRACTICES ;
    euai:relatedTo euai:TFEU .

euai:PROVIDER a owl:NamedIndividual,
        euai:Actor ;
    rdfs:label "PROVIDER"@en ;
    skos:definition "A \"Provider\" is defined as any natural or legal person, public authority, agency, or other body that develops an AI system or a general-purpose AI (GPAI) model—or has one developed—and subsequently places it on the market or puts it into service under its own name or trademark. This definition encompasses entities regardless of whether the system is provided for payment or free of charge. Furthermore, the definition includes entities established in third countries if the output of their system i"@en ;
    euai:cooperatesWith euai:MARKET_SURVEILLANCE_AUTHORITY,
