euai:MARKET_SURVEILLANCE_AUTHORITY a owl:NamedIndividual,
        euai:Authority ;
    rdfs:label "MARKET SURVEILLANCE AUTHORITY"@en ;
    skos:definition """The Market Surveillance Authority refers to the national competent authority or regulatory body designated by Member States to enforce, supervise, and implement the provisions of the AI Act. Acting as the primary point of contact for the enforcement of the Regulation, these bodies exercise their powers independently and impartially to ensure the safety, conformity, and compliance of AI systems within the Union market.

In their capacity as market regulators, these authorities are responsible for"""@en ;
